# Custom GitHub Pages Deployment Configuration

This repository uses a custom deployment workflow for GitHub Pages.

- Deployment workflow: .github/workflows/deploy.yml
- Source branch: deploy-002
- Deployment branch: gh-pages

Do not modify the GitHub Pages settings through the repository settings page.
All changes to the deployment process should be made through the workflow files.

## How it works

1. The source code is pushed to the `deploy-002` branch
2. The GitHub Actions workflow builds the project
3. The built files are deployed to the `gh-pages` branch
4. GitHub Pages serves the content from the `gh-pages` branch

## Preventing automatic deployments

The `.github/workflows/disable-default-pages.yml` workflow prevents GitHub
from automatically building and deploying the site when commits are pushed.
This is necessary because we want to use our custom build process instead. 